    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The phrase \"spooky action at a distance\" was coined by Albert Einstein to express his skepticism about the counterintuitive idea that measuring one particle could instantaneously affect another far away, seemingly violating the speed of light limit for information transfer. So, Einstein used \"spooky\" to suggest he didn't believe nature worked that way, hoping a local hidden variable explanation existed instead. Ironically, subsequent experiments have confirmed that quantum entanglement occurs exactly as described by quantum mechanics, but at the speed of light itself.",
